transaction.comments: The 2nd round pick from Rolling Rockers will most likely be the 1st pick in the 2nd round.

Just wondering if you're interested in Norwood as a nice handcuff to Turner.  Heck, in this league Norwood's practically a starter.  Not looking for too much in return.  Tossed Mason in there cause he's expensive and only 1 year.  Feel free to counter or email.

K.Smith will only start this week against the stout TEN D! After that his value is very minimal, like it has been..... throw one of your 3rd rounders in(you have 2) and it will be a deal!!! Scaife is getting all the looks in TEN at TE, he could help your run to a title sitting at 7-1 like you are.
I see you need a TE.  I've got one to spare for your 3rd rounder.
Again... I am not a fan of trading future 1st round picks.... this would get you into the 1st this year and a solid prospect in Boss, especially since Shockey is on his way out of NY.
